main event: A civilian reported seeing a single disc-shaped object hovering and moving in the sky over Dobbston, Ohio on May 10, 1966.
interesting points: The object emitted a low pulsating humming sound, similar to a jet engine.
The object appeared to be disc-shaped and glowing from within, not brilliantly shining.
The object seemed to glide with little or no visible means of propulsion.
The witness called his sister-in-law and son to also observe the object, but they had differing accounts.
The witness reported that the birds in the area seemed to be disturbed by the object's presence.
